Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges 
(no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. 
Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then 
spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, 
turning halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} lengthways and remove the core and seeds. Slice the 
@halloumi{250} into 2 slices per person. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} 
then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Trim, peel and coarsely grate the 
@carrot{1}. Pop the lettuce and carrot in a #bowl{} and set aside.

When the potatoes have 20 mins left lay the pepper halves, cut side down, on another 
#tray{}. Drizzle over a little @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and roast 
in your oven for the remainder of the potato cooking time.

> The peppers should go soft and slightly charred at the edges.

When the potatoes have 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} 
on medium-high heat. When hot, lay in the halloumi slices and fry until golden brown, 
~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> MOD: If adding bacon to your halloumi burger (15 mins before potatoes are cooked),
> heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on medium-high heat, lay in the bacon
> rashers and fry until crispy, 2-3 mins each side. Remove to a plate covered in
> kitchen roll, then cook the halloumi in the same pan as instructed in the step above.

Meanwhile, stir half the @mayonnaise{2} into the lettuce and carrot and season with a 
good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cut the @burger buns{2} in half.

When the potatoes and peppers have 2-3 mins left, pop the buns into the oven to warm 
through and toast slightly. Remove the halloumi pan from the heat and drizzle in half 
the @sweet chilli sauce{32}. Carefully turn the halloumi slices to coat them in the 
chilli sauce.

To assemble the burgers, spread a little of the remaining mayo on the base of each 
bun. Top with a slice of halloumi, the roasted pepper and another slice of halloumi. 
Drizzle with the remaining sweet chilli sauce then pop the bun lid on top. Serve with 
wedges and salad alongside.

> MOD: If adding bacon to your halloumi burger, lay a rasher of @?British streaky bacon{4} 
> on top of each halloumi slice when you assemble it. Enjoy!